503. Next Greater Element II

Given a circular integer array nums (i.e., the next element of nums[nums.length - 1] is nums[0]), return the next greater number for every element in nums.

The next greater number of a number x is the first greater number to its traversing-order next in the array, which means you could search circularly to find its next greater number. If it doesn't exist, return -1 for this number.

Example 1:

Input: nums = [1,2,1]
Output: [2,-1,2]

class Solution {
    public int[] nextGreaterElements(int[] nums)
    {
        int [] res=new int [nums.length];
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++)
        {
            res[i]=-1;
            for(int j=0;j<nums.length*2;j++)
            {
                int n=(i+j)%nums.length;
                if(nums[i]<nums[n] )
                {
                    res[i]=nums[n] ;
                    break;
                }
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
}

❌ Brute Force Code (your logic explained)
class Solution {
    public int[] nextGreaterElements(int[] nums)
    {
        int n = nums.length;
        int[] res = new int[n];

        // check for every element
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            res[i] = -1; // default if no greater element found

            // traverse circularly (2*n range)
            for (int j = 1; j < 2 * n; j++)
            {
                int idx = (i + j) % n;

                // if next greater element found
                if (nums[i] < nums[idx])
                {
                    res[i] = nums[idx];
                    break;
                }
            }
        }

        return res;
    }
}

| Approach                    | Idea                                                          | Time Complexity (TC) | Space Complexity (SC)       | Explanation                               |
| --------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------- | --------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| ❌ Brute Force               | For each index, check next 2n elements using circular loop    | **O(n²)**            | **O(1)** (excluding output) | Each element scans almost full array      |
| ✅ Optimal (Monotonic Stack) | Use stack to store decreasing elements while traversing twice | **O(n)**             | **O(n)**                    | Each element pushed & popped at most once |
